-- Gazprom Signs Agreement With Siemens to Widen Cooperation
-- Lucian Kim
-- 2008-04-03T14:03:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2008-04-03/gazprom-signs-agreement-with-siemens-to-widen-cooperation.html

          
          
             OAO Gazprom, the world's largest
natural-gas producer, agreed with  Siemens AG (SIE)  to widen
cooperation in Russia and other countries.  
 Gazprom Chief Executive Officer  Alexei Miller  and his
Siemens counterpart, Peter Loescher, signed the agreement in
Moscow today, the Russian company said in an e-mailed statement.  
 Siemens, Europe's biggest engineering company, has been
cooperating with Gazprom since 1993, according to the statement.  
